  "text": "To develop HCC in the background of liver fibrosis, we attempted to induce fibrosis in livers expressing cMyc plus shp53 via treatment with carbon tetrachloride (CCl 4 ), a hepatotoxic chemical that induces chronic liver damage [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . Mice were hydrodynamically injected with transposons encoding cMyc plus shp53, and assigned randomly to the CCl 4 and vehicle-treated groups (n = 10 for each group). Treatment was started at 15 d PHI and performed twice per week throughout the experiment (Fig. 2a) . Cells transfected with cMyc and shp53 remained as single cells at 15 d PHI and no lesions were observed in the livers (Additional file 1). As a control (referred to as 'CT'), 10 mice were treated with CCl 4 without hydrodynamic injection.",
